  "prompt": "Will there be a cure for herpes?",
  "response": "As of now, there is no definitive cure for herpes simplex virus (HSV), which includes both HSV-1 (commonly associated with oral herpes) and HSV-2 (commonly associated with genital herpes). Current treatments focus on managing symptoms and reducing the frequency of outbreaks. Antiviral medications, like acyclovir, valacyclovir, and famciclovir, can help control the virus and alleviate symptoms.\n\nResearch into potential cures and vaccines for herpes is ongoing, and there are promising developments, but no effective cure has been established yet. It's important to stay informed through reputable medical sources and consult with healthcare providers for the latest research and treatment options. If you have specific concerns, talking to a medical professional can provide personalized advice and information.",
